Bean Externalization (reading from properties file)
1. Properties file is a global file that stores key-value pairs that can be referenced 
   in the application 
2. Properties file allows code (like connection properties) to be changed once, and not 
   having to retype it everywhere in the application 


3 Steps to reading properties file
1. Create the properties file
2. Link the properties 
3. Inject the properties in xml config file